ave a maximum of 8 MFA devices assigned.",nc="Use MFA to increase the security of your AWS environment. Signing in with MFA requires an authentication code from an MFA device. Each user can have a maximum of 1 MFA device assigned.",cc="Save your user name and password or download the credentials file.",lc="Generate a user name and password you can use to authenticate to Amazon Keyspaces. You can have a maximum of two sets of credentials (active or inactive) at a time.",uc="New X.509 certificate created. Download your private key file. You cannot retrieve it later.",dc="For your protection, store your private key file and certificate securely and do not share them.",pc="Use the <a>AWS CLI V2</a> and enable authentication through a user in IAM Identity Center.",mc="Rotate access keys regularly.",hc="For more details about managing access keys, see the <link>best practices for managing AWS access keys</link>.",yc="Access key best practices",gc="Create user group",vc="User group name",fc='A user group named "{userGroupName}" already exists. Use a different user group name.',Ac="Create a user group and select policies to attach to the group. We recommend using groups to manage user permissions by job function, AWS service access, or custom permissions.",Sc="An IAM user is an entity that you create in AWS to represent the person or application that uses it to interact with AWS.",Ec="You can attach up to {number} policies to this user group. All the users in this group will have permissions that are defined in the selected policies.",Ic="Delete <b>{groupsNum} user groups</b> permanently? All the users in these groups will lose the group permissions.",wc="User group deleted.",Cc="User group deleting.",bc="User group not deleted.",_c="User groups not deleted.",Pc="Add users",Tc="Remove {user} from group?",Rc="This user will lose the group permissions.",Mc="These users will lose the group permissions.",Dc="1 user removed from this group.",Nc="{count} users removed from this g