pport only Sigv4 based signatures on Amazon Web Services requests",PA="Session tokens from the STS endpoint in the AWS GovCloud (US-East) Region support the use of the Sigv4a algorithm <a> Learn more </a> when signing Amazon Web Services requests. By default, session tokens from the STS endpoint in the AWS GovCloud (US-West) Region support only the Sigv4 algorithm for generating signatures. If you intend to use Sigv4a to cryptographically sign your Amazon Web Services requests, you can configure the STS endpoint in the AWS GovCloud (US-West) Region to vend session tokens that also support the Sigv4a algorithm.",TA="Change AWS request signature compatibility of session tokens from the AWS GovCloud (US-West) Region STS endpoint.",RA="Session tokens from the AWS GovCloud (US-West) Region STS endpoint support AWS request signatures using:",MA="AWS GovCloud (US-East) Region endpoint",DA="Support only Sigv4 based signatures on AWS requests",NA="Support both Sigv4 and Sigv4a based signatures on AWS requests",OA="By default, session tokens from the STS endpoint in the AWS US ISOB East (Ohio) Region support only the Sigv4 algorithm for generating signatures. If you intend to use Sigv4a to cryptographically sign your AWS requests <a> Learn more </a>, you can configure the STS endpoint in the AWS US ISOB East (Ohio) Region to vend session tokens that also support the Sigv4a algorithm.",LA="Change AWS request signature compatibility of session tokens from the AWS US ISOB East (Ohio) Region STS endpoint.",UA="Session tokens from the AWS US ISOB East (Ohio) Region STS endpoint support AWS request signatures using:",kA="AWS US ISOB East (Ohio) Region endpoint",xA="Session tokens from the STS endpoint in the AWS US ISO West Region support the use of the Sigv4 algorithm <a> Learn more </a> when signing AWS requests. By default, session tokens from the STS endpoint in the AWS US ISO East Region support only the Sigv4 algorithm for generating signatures. If you intend to use Sigv4a to