lso allow password recovery for specific member accounts.",lb="Password recovery through the forgot password flow will be blocked for root users of all your member accounts with no root user credentials. {learnMore}",ub="Learn more about password recovery",db="You can take certain root actions in member accounts like deleting misconfigured policies in Amazon SQS, or Amazon S3.",pb="When you enable root access management, you enable trusted access for IAM in AWS Organizations. {learnMore}",mb="Learn more about trusted access",hb="Capabilities",yb="Specify how you'd like to control root access for your organization's member accounts, being in a management or delegated admin account. You can also change this later after enabling root access control for your organization.",gb="Delegated administrator for centralized root access- <i>recommended</i>",vb="In addition to the management account, this member account will be authorized to have centralized root access for other member accounts.",fb="Info about Root access management",Ab="Centralize root access for your member accounts",Sb="Self service privileged root-only tasks",Eb="You can delete root credentials for member accounts and perform privileged actions from the management or delegated account. <a>Learn more about centralizing root access</a>",Ib="Update delegated administrator",wb="Delegate the privilege to another member account to centrally manage root access for all member accounts in Organization {organizationId}",Cb="The delegated administrator account specified below can manage root access management on your behalf. You can update this to delegate this privilege to another AWS account in your organization.",bb="Assign delegated administrator",_b="Delegate the privilege to a member account to centrally manage root access for all member accounts in Organization {organizationId}",Pb="Assign",Tb="The member account you specify below can manage root access management on your behalf. You can remove, or change this to any other member account later.",Rb="Info about selected capabilities",Mb="At least one selection is required",Db="Capabilities to enable",Nb="Root access management enabled. You can now delete root user credentials for member accounts from the AWS accounts page.",Ob="Root access management enabled. You can now delete root user credentials for member accounts from the Root access management page.",Lb="Enabling root access management.",Ub="Root access management not enabled.",kb="Removing AWS account {accountId} as a delegated administrator.",xb="Remove delegated administrator for centralized root access.",zb="We recommend not to use the management account for managing root access of your member accounts, but delegate this privilege to a member account. You can update the setting to delegate this privilege to another member account in your organization.",Wb="Info about Delegated administrator for centralized root access",Fb="Use a member account of your organization for managing root access on other member accounts. You can update the setting to delegate this privilege to another member account in your organization.",Gb="Delegated administrator for centralized root access",Vb="Delegated administration account",Kb="Account ID: {id}",Bb="Disable privileged root actions",Yb="Disable",Hb="Disable privileged root actions in member accounts.",qb="You will lose the privilege of taking root actions in member accounts, while being in a management or delegated administrator account.",jb="Disable centralized root access",$b="Disable centralized root access for your member accounts.",Qb="You will lose all settings and preferences for centralized root access. All member accounts with no root credentials will be unblocked from password recovery.",Jb='To confirm disablement, type "{confirmPhrase}".',Xb="Disable root credentials management",Zb="Disable root credentials management.",e_="All member accounts with no root user credentials will be unblocked from password recovery.",t_