Y_="Hello,{newline}{newline}You now have access to the AWS Management Console for the account ending in {accountEndsIn}. {newline}{newline}------{newline}{newline}Sign-in URL: {consoleSignInURL}{newline}User name: {userName}{newline}{newline}Your password will be provided separately by your AWS account administrator. {newline}{newline}------{newline}{newline}Stay connected with AWS by creating a profile: https://pages.awscloud.com/IAM-communication-preferences.html{newline}{newline}Sincerely,{newline}Your AWS Account Administrator",H_="Email sign-in instructions",q_="Console sign-in details",j_="Copy permissions",$_="Attach policies directly",Q_="Are you providing console access to a person? Instead of creating an IAM user, we recommend that your management account owner enable Identity Center for your organization so you can use an organizational directory to manage people's access to AWS accounts and applications.",J_="Are you providing console access to a person? Instead of creating an IAM user, we recommend that you add the person to your organization’s directory. To do so, you must be signed in as either the organization management account or the delegated administrator.",X_="We recommend that you use Identity Center to provide console access to a person. With Identity Center, you can centrally manage user access to their AWS accounts and cloud applications. To do so, you must be signed in to the Identity Center console using the credentials of the management account in AWS Organizations. If you aren't the management account owner, contact the owner to perform this task.",Z_="best practice (opens in a new tab)",eP="best practice",tP="In addition to console access, users with SignInLocalDevelopmentAccess permissions can use the same console credentials for programmatic access without the need for access keys.",aP="If you're providing console access to a person, it's a {link} to manage their access in IAM Identity Center.",sP="Sign in from the AWS access portal - Recommended",iP="Specify a user in Identity Center - Recommended",oP="Sign in to this AWS account only",rP="I want to create an IAM user",nP="An IAM user is created in this account. As a best practice, create IAM users only if you need to enable programmatic access through access keys, service-specific credentials for AWS CodeCommit or Amazon Keyspaces, or a backup credential for emergency account access.",cP="Choose how you want this person to access AWS",lP="Enable console access - <i>optional</i>",uP="Do you want to provide console access to a person?",dP="Autogenerated password",pP="Custom password",mP="For programmatic access, you can generate access keys after you create the user.",hP="Manage in Identity Center. Opens in a new tab.",yP="Specify a user in Identity Center",gP="This will take you to the AWS Identity Center console.",vP="- <i>optional</i>",fP="Console password type",AP="Group policy was not attached.",SP="User was not added to group.",EP="This is the only time these SMTP credentials can be viewed or downloaded. You cannot recover them later. However, you can create new credentials at any time.",IP="User created with a few errors",wP="See error description above. This is the only time these SMTP credentials can be viewed or downloaded. You cannot recover them later. However, you can create new credentials at any time.",CP="Return to SES console",bP="Retrieve SMTP credentials",_P="This is the only time you can view and download these SMTP security credentials. Never share your SMTP credentials with anyone.",PP="IAM user name",TP="SMTP user name",RP="{iamUserName}_credentials.csv",MP="This page cannot be loaded",DP="A new user group will be created.",NP="The new user will be added to a new user group with the permissions attached to the user group.",OP="This permissions policy gives the user permissions to access AWS SES.",LP="SMTP credentials",UP="User Name",kP="Create an IAM user with SMTP credentials for SMTP authentication with Amazon SES.",xP="