ns",ET="Security recommendations",IT="Add MFA",wT="Sign in as the root user (or contact your administrator) and register a multi-factor authentication (MFA) device for the root user to improve security for this account.",CT="Having multi-factor authentication (MFA) for the root user improves security for this account.",bT="Root user has MFA",_T="Having multi-factor authentication (MFA) for the IAM user improves security for this account.",PT="Updating tags",TT="Info on adding tags",RT="Tags for {name}",MT="Audience selection",DT="All audiences",NT="AWS secures communication with OIDC identity providers (IdPs) using our library of trusted Certificate Authorities (CAs). If your IdP relies on a certificate that isn't signed by one of these trusted CAs, then we secure communication using the thumbprints you specify.",OT="SAML provider details",LT="API key name",UT="API key",kT="Download API Key",xT="Retrieve your API key that you can use to authenticate to {service}.",zT="Retrieve API key",WT="Generate an API key you can use to authenticate to {service}.",FT="Generate API key",GT="Credentials activated.",VT="Credentials deactivated.",KT="Activating credentials...",BT="Deactivating credentials...",YT="Creating credentials.",HT="Credentials deleted.",qT="Deleting credentials.",jT="Resetting credentials.",$T="No credentials",QT="Credential selection",JT="Service specific credential",XT="SSH public keys for AWS CodeCommit",ZT="Deactivating SSH public key...",eR="Deleting SSH public key...",tR="Use SSH public keys to authenticate access to AWS CodeCommit repositories. You can have a maximum of five SSH public keys (active or inactive) at a time.",aR="No SSH public keys",sR="SSH Key ID",iR="Uploaded",oR="SSH public key selection",rR="SSH public key",nR="CloudFront key pairs",cR="You use key pairs in Amazon CloudFront to create signed URLs. You can have a maximum of two CloudFront key pairs (active or inactive) at a time.",lR="Deleting cloudfront key pair...",uR="Cloudfront ke