 using this API key will immediately lose access.",aM="5 days",sM="365 days",iM="Never expires",oM="Set duration of key validity to enhance security and limit exposure if the key is compromised. If you set an expiration, the key will automatically expire after the duration you specify. You cannot activate the same key later again.",rM="Specify API key expiry in days",nM="Enter custom duration in days",cM="Long-term API key generated successfully.",lM="Copy your API key now. You won't be able to retrieve it later.",uM="Unable to download credentials file",dM="Code copied",pM="API keys grant access to specific AWS services. You can have a maximum of two API keys per service (active, inactive, or expired) at a time.",mM="Maximum limit of two keys reached for all available services",hM="Successfully activated API key {key} for {service}",yM="Successfully deactivated API key {key} for {service}",gM="Successfully deleted API key {key} for {service}",vM="Error activating API key {key} for {service}",fM="Error deactivating API key {key} for {service}",AM="Error reseting API key {key} for {service}",SM="Activate {username} for {service}",EM="Activate API key {username} for {service}?",IM="Deactivate {username} for {service}",wM="Delete {username} for {service}",CM="Delete API key {username} for {service} permanently? You cannot undo this action later.",bM="Successfully generated API key for {service}",_M="API keys provide programmatic access to specific AWS services. Store your key securely — it will not be shown again after generation.",PM="Choose the AWS service this API key will authenticate to.",TM="Choose a service",RM="Policy {policyName} set as permissions boundary on {number} entities.",MM="Changing permissions boundary...",DM="Permissions boundary not changed.",NM="Setting this policy as a permissions boundary for the selected entities limits the maximum permissions they have.",OM="Policies in IAM",LM="You manage access in AWS by creating policies and attaching them