onsole access disabled.",hN="Console access updated with a few errors. See error description below.",yN="Console access updated.",gN="Console access was not updated.",vN="Console access enabled with a few errors. See error description below.",fN="Console access was not enabled.",AN="Manage {userName}'s AWS console access and password.",SN="Console access",EN="Set password",IN="Keep existing password",wN="You have successfully enabled the user's new password.",CN="This is the only time you can view this password. After you close this window, if the password is lost, you must create a new one.",bN="Used today",_N="Used",PN="Access key created",TN="Best practice",RN="Deactivate/delete access keys not in use.",MN="Enabled with MFA",DN="Enable MFA",NN="Access key 1",ON="Never. Password enabled",LN="Today",UN="Console password age",kN="Refresh users list",xN="Programmatic access with access key",zN="Private key added successfully.",WN="Failed to add private key.",FN="Add key",GN="Encryption preference updated successfully.",VN="Edit encryption preference",KN="SAML assertion encryption",BN="Required",YN="AWS will only accept SAML assertions encrypted with your key.",HN="Allowed",qN="AWS will accept unencrypted SAML assertions as well as those encrypted with your key.",jN="Key ID",$N="Added on",QN="Preference for accepting or rejecting unencrypted SAML assertions.",JN="Encryption preference",XN="AWS will accept unencrypted SAML assertions as well as those encrypted with a key you specify.",ZN="You can have a maximum of 2 private keys. Your identity provider will use the public key from the X.509 certificates for encrypting the SAML assertions. If you don’t specify any key, AWS will accept only unencrypted SAML assertions.",eO="Private keys for SAML decryption ({count})",tO="No keys specified",aO="Encrypted SAML assertions aren't supported for Amazon Cognito Identity pools. If you use this SAML provider in Amazon Cognito, any encrypted assertions will be rejected. <a> Learn more about using identity provider in Amazon Cognito </a>",sO="Specify the private key you want IAM to use for decrypting the SAML assertion. To use encrypted SAML, you will need to set up your external Identity provider to encrypt SAML assertions using your public key, and configure your external Identity provider to use the dedicated Sign-in URL for this IDP in IAM. The dedicated Sign-in URL will be generated after the IDP is created in AWS.",iO="Private key file",oO="IAM will use this key for decrypting your SAML assertions.",rO="Must be a .pem file",nO="Private key is required.",cO="If checked, AWS will not accept non-encrypted SAML assertions.",lO="Require encryption",uO="Private Key {privateKeyId} removed successfully.",dO="Failed to remove private key {privateKeyId}",pO="Remove private key",mO="AWS needs at least one private key if SAML assertion encryption is required. Update your encryption preference if you still want to remove this key.",hO="Remove private key <b>{privateKeyId}</b>?",yO="Permissions boundary removed on {name}.",gO="Permissions boundary removed on {number} entities.",vO="Permissions boundary not removed.",fO="Set this policy as a permissions boundary",AO="Detach <b>{name}</b> policy?",SO="Detach permissions policy from <b>{number} entities</b>?",EO="{entityName} will lose all the permissions defined in this policy.",IO="The {number} entities will lose all the permissions defined in this policy.",wO="Policy detached from {name}.",CO="Policy detached from {number} entities.",bO="Detaching policy...",_O="Detach {name}?",PO="Attach",TO="Policy not attached to any entity.",RO='Provide a valid {refType}. The {refType} must be "{branch}" or "{tag}".',MO="Password recovery allowed for AWS Account {accountId}. The root user can now recover their password through the forgot password flow.",DO="Allowing password recovery for AWS Account {accountId}.",NO="Access keys last used",OO="Permanently delete root user credentials on account <b>account</b>?",LO='To confirm deletion, type "{confirmPhrase}".',UO="Console password last used",kO="Root credentials deleted for AWS Account {accountId}.",xO="Deleting root user credentials for AWS Account {accountId}.",zO="Review root user console password and access keys last used information and delete all root user credentials.",WO="Root credentials including root access keys, password, and signing certificates for the specific member account will be deleted, and multi-factor authentication (MFA) will be deleted. You will no longer be able to sign in as root in that account. You can perform privileged root-only actions as shown in this page using short term root sessions. You will not be able to recover the account's root user credentials through the standard recovery flow using forgot password link on the sign-in page. <a>Learn more about recovering root user credentials</a>",FO="Delete bucket policy",GO="Permanently delete policy on bucket {bucket}?",VO="Copy and save the bucket policy if needed because this action will permanently delete the policy.",KO="Bucket policy",BO="S3 bucket URI is required.",YO="S3 bucket URI is invalid.",HO="Bucket policy on S3 bucket {bucket} deleted.",qO="Deleting bucket policy on S3 bucket {bucket}.",jO="Bucket policy on S3 bucket {bucket} not deleted.",$O="Specify S3 bucket to delete its bucket policy. You can preview and copy to save the bucket policy before deleting it.",QO="Delete SQS policy",JO="Permanently delete policy on queue {queue}?",XO="Copy and save the queue policy if needed because this action will permanently delete the policy.",ZO="SQS queue ARN is invalid.",eL="SQS policy on {queue} not deleted.",tL="SQS queue ARN",aL="View details",sL="The maximum number of groups per user is exceeded for user: {name}.",iL="Other groups",oL="There are no groups selected.",rL="There are no permissions selected.",nL="The selected policies exceed this account's quota",cL="The selected groups exceed this account's quota",lL="The following policies will be attached to this user.",uL="{count} inline policies added",dL="1 inline policy added",pL="Permissions copied from <b>{name}</b>",mL="{count} policies added to {userName}",hL="1 policy added",yL="Failed to add permissions to <b>{userName}</b>",gL="Loading summary",vL="Removing the permissions boundary might expand the user's permissions, allowing the user to perform all actions granted in its permissions policies.",fL="Remove permissions for user?",AL="Remove policy <b>{policy}</b>?",SL="Remove policies",EL="Remove policy",IL="Enable console access for {userName}.",wL="User automatically gets the following inline policy attached, to revoke their active sessions.",CL="revoke older sessions policy preview",bL="Permissions boundary <b>{boundary}</b> added.",_L="Permissions boundary changed to <b>{boundary}</b>.",PL="Setting permissions boundary.",TL="Failed to change permissions boundary.",RL="There is no policy selected.",ML={"iam.navigation.header":"Identity and Access Management (IAM)","iam.navigation.dashboard":"Dashboard","iam.navigation.access_manager":"Access Management","iam.navigation.groups":"IAM user groups","iam.navigation.users":"IAM users","iam.navigation.roles":"Roles","iam.navigation.policies":"Policies","iam.navigation.permission_policies":"Policies","iam.navigation.identity_providers":"Identity providers","iam.navigation.account_settings":"Account settings","iam.navigation.policysim":"Policy simulator","iam.navigation.credential_report":"Credential report","iam.navigation.organization_activity":"Organization activity","iam.navigation.service_control_policies":"Service control policies","iam.navigation.resource_control_policies":"Resource control policies","iam.navigation.armor_control_policies":"Armor control policies","iam.navigation.access_reports":"Access reports","iam.navigation.access_analyzer":"Access Analyzer","iam.navigation.access_analyzer.rules":"Archive rules","iam.navigation.access_analyzer.analyzers":"Analyzers","iam.navigation.access_analyzer.settings":"Settings","iam.navigation.aws_account":"AWS Account","iam.navigation.aws_organization":"AWS Organizations","iam.copyLable":"Copy {resource}","iam.copySuccess":"{resource} Copied","iam.copyFailed":"Failed to copy {resource}","iam.newConsole.header":"Introducing the new {module} experience","iam.newConsole.content":"We’ve redesigned the {module} experience to make it easier to use.","iam.newConsole.feedbackLabel":"Let us know what you think","accessDenied.header":"Access denied","accessDenied.errorDeny":"You don't have permission to perform this action.","accessDenied.defaultDeny":"You don't have permission to {service}:{action}. {customErrorMessagePlaceholder} To request access, copy the following text and send it to your AWS administrator.","accessDenied.userField":"User:","accessDenied.serviceField":"Service:","accessDenied.actionField":"Action:","accessDenied.resourceField":"On resource(s):","accessDenied.contextField":"Context:","accessDenied.requestCopied":"Access details copied","accessDenied.copyButton":"Copy","accessDenied.learnMore":"Learn more about troubleshooting access denied errors.","global.defaults.info":"Info","home.consoleName":"AWS IAM Console","home.consoleDescription":"AWS IAM Console Description","idp.list.pageTitle":"Identity Providers","idp.create.pageTitle":"Create Identity Provider","idp.cancel":"Cancel","idp.delete":"Delete","idp.next":"Next","idp.replace":"Replace","idp.assignRole":"Assign role","idp.assignRole.modalTitle":"Assign role for {idpName}","idp.assignRole.labelForCreateNew":"Create a new role","idp.assignRole.labelForExistingRole":"Use an existing role","idp.assignRole.descriptionForCreateNew":"Create a new role for this identity provider and add permissions to the new role.","idp.assignRole.descriptionForExistingRole":"Associate an existing role by adding this IdP to the trusted entities of the role.","idp.delete.modalTitle":"Delete {idpName}?","idp.delete.removeDisclaimer1":"Identities from this provi