s, such as access keys, in your applications.</p><p>To use an IdP, create an IAM identity provider entity to establish a trust relationship between your AWS account and the IdP. IAM supports IdPs that are compatible with <openid>OpenID Connect (OIDC)</openid> or <samlLink>SAML 2.0 (Security Assertion Markup Language 2.0)</samlLink>.</p>","idp.default.help.linkText":"Identity Providers and Federation","idp.tag.updateSuccess":"Tags updated.","idp.tag.updating":"Updating tags...","idp.tag.updateError":"Tags not updated.","idp.tag.breadcrumbTitle":"Manage tags","idp.google.magic.provider.warning":"AWS secures communication with Google’s OIDC identity provider (IdP) using our library of trusted CAs rather than using a certificate thumbprint to verify the server certificate of your IdP. Your legacy thumbprint(s) will remain in your configuration but will no longer be needed for validation.","idp.s3.magic.provider.warning":"AWS secures communication with OIDC identity providers (IdP) that use an S3 bucket to host the JSON Web Key Set (JWKS) endpoint using our library of trusted CAs rather than using a certificate thumbprint to verify your IdP’s server certificate. Your legacy thumbprint(s) will remain in your configuration but will no longer be needed for validation.","idp.auth0.magic.provider.warning":"AWS secures communication with this OIDC identity provider (IdP) using our library of trusted CAs rather than using a certificate thumbprint to verify the server certificate of your IdP. Your legacy thumbprint(s) will remain in your configuration but will no longer be needed for validation.","errorMapper.codeTitle.limitExceeded":"Limit exceeded","errorMapper.codeTitle.invalidInput":"Invalid input","errorMapper.codeTitle.noSuchEntity":"Entity does not exist","errorMapper.codeTitle.internalFailure":"Something went wrong","errorMapper.codeTitle.accessDenied":"You need permissions","errorMapper.codeTitle.entityAlreadyExists":"Entity already exists","errorMapper.codeDescription.