geHeader":"User groups","group.default.help.pageBody":'<p>A user group is a collection of IAM users. User groups simplify permissions management by letting you grant, change, and remove permissions for multiple users at once. For example, you can create a user group named "Admins" and give that group administrative permissions. Any user in that group automatically has the permissions that are assigned to the group.</p>',"group.default.help.usergroups":"IAM user groups","group.default.help.create":"Creating user groups","group.default.help.manage":"Managing user groups","group.list.help.learnMoreText":"Learn more","group.list.help.pageHeader":"User groups","group.list.help.pageBody":'<p>A user group is a collection of IAM users. User groups simplify permissions management by letting you grant, change, and remove permissions for multiple users at once. For example, you can create a user group named "Admins" and give that group administrative permissions. Any user in that group automatically has the permissions that are assigned to the group.</p>',"group.list.help.usergroups":"IAM user groups","group.list.help.create":"Creating user groups","group.list.help.manage":"Managing user groups","group.detail.help.learnMoreText":"Learn more","group.detail.help.pageHeader":"User groups","group.detail.help.pageBody":'<p>A user group is a collection of IAM users. User groups simplify permissions management by letting you grant, change, and remove permissions for multiple users at once. For example, you can create a user group named "Admins" and give that group administrative permissions. Any user in that group automatically has the permissions that are assigned to the group.</p>',"group.detail.help.usergroups":"IAM user groups","group.detail.help.create":"Creating user groups","group.detail.help.manage":"Managing user groups","group.create.help.learnMoreText":"Learn more","group.create.help.pageHeader":"User groups","group.create.help.pageBody":'<p>A user group is a collection of IAM users. User groups simplify permissions management by letting you grant, change, and remove permissions for multiple users at once. For example, you can create a user group named "Admins" and give that group administrative permissions. Any user in that group automatically has the permissions that are assigned to the group.</p>',"group.create.help.usergroups":"IAM user groups","group.create.help.create":"Creating user groups","group.create.help.manage":"Managing user groups","group.detail.addUser.help.learnMoreText":"Learn more","group.detail.addUser.help.pageHeader":"IAM users","group.detail.addUser.help.pageBody":"<p>An AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) user is an entity that you create in AWS to represent the person or application that uses it to interact with AWS. A user in AWS consists of a name and credentials. </p>","group.detail.addUser.help.users":"Adding and removing users in an IAM group","group.detail.attachPolicy.help.learnMoreText":"Learn more","group.detail.attachPolicy.help.pageHeader":"Permissions","group.detail.attachPolicy.help.pageBody":"<p>You manage access in AWS by creating policies and attaching them to IAM identities (users, groups of users, or roles) or AWS resources. A policy is an object in AWS that, when associated with an identity or resource, defines their permissions.</p>","group.detail.attachPolicy.help.policies":"Policies and permissions","group.detail.attachPolicy.help.attachPolicies":"Attaching a policy to an IAM User group","group.detail.attachPolicy.help.managedPolicies":"Managed policies","group.create.addUser.help.learnMoreText":"Learn more","group.create.addUser.help.pageHeader":"IAM users","group.create.addUser.help.pageBody":"<p>An AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) user is an entity that you create in AWS to represent the person or application that uses it to interact with AWS. A user in AWS consists of a name and credentials. </p>","group.create.addUser.help.usergroups":"Creating User groups","group.create.addUser.help.users":"Adding and removing users in an IAM group","util.selected":"Selected","util.simulate":"Simulate","group.delete.errorDetails.header":"Errors deleting groups.","group.delete.errorDetails.template":"{name} not deleted.","group.details.removePolicies.errorDetails.header":"Errors removing permissions from this group.","group.details.removePolicies.errorDetails.template":"Permission {name} not removed.","group.details.removeUserFromGroup.errorDetails.header":"Errors removing users from this group.","group.details.removeUserFromGroup.errorDetails.template":"User {name} not removed.","group.add.users.errorDetails.header":"Errors adding users to the group.","group.add.users.errorDetails.template":"User {name} not added.","group.add.policies.errorDetails.header":"Errors attaching policies to the group.","group.add.policies.errorDetails.template":"Policy {name} not added.","group.search.placeholder":"Filter User groups by property or group name and press enter","policies.search.placeholder":"Filter policies by property or policy name and press enter","group.attach.policy.exceedLimit":"Number of policies to be attached exceeds the limit.","table.groupValueText":"Values","role.search.placeholder":"Filter roles by property or role name and press enter","role.list.numberOfRoles":"{number} roles","role.list.roleName":"Role name","role.list.path":"Path","role.list.Description":"Description","role.list.trustEntities":"Trusted entities","role.list.creationTime":"Creation time","role.list.ARN":"ARN","role.list.lastActivity":"Last activity","role.list.duration":"Max CLI/API session","role.list.tableHeader":"Roles","role.list.cupcake.tableHeader":"IAM roles","role.list.tableHeaderDescription":"An IAM role is an identity you can create that has specific permissions with credentials that are valid for short durations. Roles can be assumed by entities that you trust.","role.trustEntities.AWSService":"AWS Service","role.trustEntities.Account":"Account","role.trustEntities.IdentityProvider":"Identity Provider","role.trustEntities.SLR":"Service-Linked Role","role.trustEntities.SLR.descrition":"Unique service role with permissions pre-defined by the linked service.","role.list.tableHeader.Create":"Create role","role.delete.deleted.single.roles":"Role deleted {roleName}.","role.delete.deleted.multi.roles":"Roles deleted.","role.delete.failed.single.roles":"Failed deleting role {roleName}.","role.delete.failed.multi.roles":"Failed deleting roles.","role.delete.deleting.single.roles":"Deleting role {roleName}.","role.delete.deleting.multi.roles":"Deleting roles.","role.delete.single.modalTitle":"Delete {roleName}?","role.delete.multi.modalTitle":"Delete {roleNum} roles?","role.delete.description":"This action deletes all of the following roles, along with any attached instance profiles and inline policies. Are you sure you want to delete the following roles?","role.delete.description2":"Note: Recent activity usually appears within 4 hours. Data is stored for a maximum of 365 days, depending when your region began supporting this feature.","role.delete.placeholder":"{roleNum} roles","role.delete.errorDetails.header":"Errors during deleting roles.","role.delete.errorDetails.template":"Role {name} not deleted.\\n","user.list.pageTitle":"IAM users","user.list.cupcake.pageTitle":"IAM users","user.list.tableColumnName":"User name","user.list.tableColumnName.cupcake":"IAM user name","user.list.tableColumnPath":"Path","user.list.tableColumnGroups":"Groups","user.list.tableColumnGroups.cupcake":"IAM groups","user.list.tableColumnLastActivity":"Last activity","user.list.tableColumnMfa":"MFA","user.list.tableColumnPasswordAge":"Password age","user.list.tableColumnConsoleLastSignin":"Console last sign-in","user.list.tableColumnAccessKeyId":"Access key ID","user.list.tableColumnAccessKeyAge":"Active key age","user.list.tableColumnAccessKeyLastUsed":"Access key last used","user.list.tableColumnArn":"ARN","user.list.tableColumnCreationTime":"Creation